  <data name="Faq.Title" xml:space="preserve"><value>Frequently asked questions</value></data>
  <data name="Faq.Subtitle" xml:space="preserve"><value>Everything you might want to know about Daleel.</value></data>
  <data name="Faq.Q1" xml:space="preserve"><value>What is Daleel?</value></data>
  <data name="Faq.A1" xml:space="preserve"><value>Daleel is a personal shopping assistant. Ask a question in plain English or Arabic and it searches stores, marketplaces and the open web to find products, compare prices, summarize brand reputation and surface the best deals — then gives you a clear, sourced answer.</value></data>
  <data name="Faq.Q2" xml:space="preserve"><value>Which languages does Daleel support?</value></data>
  <data name="Faq.A2" xml:space="preserve"><value>Both English and Arabic. You can ask in either language, switch the interface anytime, and the whole experience — including right-to-left layout — adapts automatically.</value></data>
  <data name="Faq.Q3" xml:space="preserve"><value>How does Daleel filter results?</value></data>
  <data name="Faq.A3" xml:space="preserve"><value>Daleel applies a halal content filter by default: results and images that include alcohol, pork, gambling, adult or other non-halal content are removed so what you see stays family-friendly. You can adjust the strictness — or, for admin accounts, turn it off — under Content Filter in Settings.</value></data>
  <data name="Faq.Q4" xml:space="preserve"><value>Is Daleel free?</value></data>
  <data name="Faq.A4" xml:space="preserve"><value>Yes — every account starts with 500 free credits each month, no credit card required. Each search spends credits based on the providers it uses, so a quick lookup costs little and a deep search costs more. If you need more, paid plans add larger monthly credit allowances, deal monitoring and saved results. See the Pricing page for details.</value></data>
  <data name="Faq.Q5" xml:space="preserve"><value>Do I need my own API keys?</value></data>
  <data name="Faq.A5" xml:space="preserve"><value>No. Daleel works out of the box. Power users can optionally add their own model and search provider keys under Settings — they stay in your browser and are never written to our server logs.</value></data>
  <data name="Faq.Q6" xml:space="preserve"><value>How is my search data used?</value></data>
  <data name="Faq.A6" xml:space="preserve"><value>Your personal search history is saved only for you, under your account. Separately, searches are analyzed anonymously to improve results — we record what was searched, the market, timing and cost, but never anything that identifies you. Analytics and cost logs carry only a one-way hash, so a search can't be traced back to your account.</value></data>
  <data name="Faq.Q7" xml:space="preserve"><value>How is a brand's reputation score calculated?</value></data>
  <data name="Faq.A7" xml:space="preserve"><value>Reputation is assessed for your specific market, not globally, and is grounded in live search and the brand's own pages — never invented. We weigh five factors: (1) reliability, (2) after-sales service and local service centres, (3) local warranty terms, (4) spare-parts availability, and (5) real user reviews from forums and social media. These produce a 1–5 score plus a badge. The badge rule is exact: "Strong local presence" = the brand has local service AND scores 4.0 or higher; "Limited local support" = no local service centre in your market (a cheap product from such a brand is usually a poor deal); otherwise no badge is shown. Local after-sales service is weighted heavily on purpose — without it, even a cheap, well-built product is a risk.</value></data>
  <data name="Footer.Privacy" xml:space="preserve"><value>Searches are analyzed anonymously to improve results.</value></data>

